y poverty studies and most likely will be found in the GAR country-study surveys. Yet, it is still true that a number of factors make current consumption a noisy welfare indicator as well. In that sense, the study can certainly be related to other dimensions such as education, nutrition and health, or even a relationship between assets and hazards can be brought into full consideration. 3. Estimation decisions and implementation \u2013 motivations and rationale.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "580ecf5c-2065-4831-a189-c8543c9a0bfc": {"__data__": {"id_": "580ecf5c-2065-4831-a189-c8543c9a0bfc", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/assessing-relationship-between-natural-hazards-and-poverty-conceptual-and-methodological-proposal", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Assessing the Relationship between Natural Hazards and Poverty \u2013 A Conceptual and Methodological Proposal", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/assessing-relationship-between-natural-hazards-and-poverty-conceptual-and-methodological-proposal", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "0103285aa48b3733d45782fa1c9d1894b1bba58bd033e684bbca4360ed2318d7"}, "2": {"node_id": "c3dea20b-3d75-4967-ba9d-e5028955e957", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/assessing-relationship-between-natural-hazards-and-poverty-conceptual-and-methodological-proposal", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nat